{"id": "duc04-testb-14:4#12", "contents": "U.S. special envoy Richard Holbrooke met with NATO Secretary General Javier Solana and Supreme Allied Commander Europe Wesley K. Clark to discuss the situation in Kosovo. Following the meeting, Holbrooke stated that the military situation in Kosovo was as dire as it was two weeks prior, despite a temporary decrease in fighting. He emphasized that the potential for renewed violence remained high, making the situation just as serious as it was a week or two ago."}
